Pour about cold @water{300%ml}(salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and @chicken stock sachet{1} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%mins}.

Once cooked, remove from the heat.

Keep covered for ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Clean the @mushrooms{250%g} with #kitchen paper{} and roughly chop.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}(trimmed). Halve lengthways then thinly slice.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Season the @pork loin steak{300%g} with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the oil is hot, sear the pork loin fat-side down until crispy, ~{2-3%mins}.

Once seared, fry until cooked, ~{4-5%mins} on each side.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{}, cover and allow to rest. IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, fry the mushrooms and leek until softened, ~{4-6%mins}, stirring occasionally.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{125%g}, @dried oregano sachet{1} and @Worcester sauce sachet{1}.

Cook until the sauce has reduced, ~{4-5%mins}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} to the sauce if you feel it's too dry.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates.

Place the pork on top.

Pour over the creamy leek and mushroom sauce.